Australia  beat West Indies by eight
wickets in the first of two Twenty20 internationals between the
teams in the Caribbean.  Shane Watsonhit 69 and  Mike Hussey  made an unbeaten 59 as
Australia scored 153-2 to chase down the West Indies total of
150-7 with 11 balls to spare in St. Lucia. Dan Christian earlier
took 3-27 to finish as the gameâ€™s best bowler.  The second match in Barbados takes place March 30 before
the teams play a best-of-three Test series starting April 7.  The five-match one-day contest ended in a 2-2 tie two days
